land>":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"Abt 1324–":"circa 1324–Overleden","1324–Female":"1324–Overleden","1330–1350":"1330–1350","1350–1415":"1350–1415","1294–Male":"1294–Overleden","1415":"1415","Abt 1350":"circa 1350","1324":"1324","1330":"1330","Abt 1324":"circa 1324","1350":"1350","1294":"1294","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","<Of, Lackham, Wiltshire, England>":"Wiltshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1324–":"about 1324–Deceased","1324–Female":"1324–Deceased","1330–1350":"1330–1350","1350–1415":"1350–1415","1294–Male":"1294–Deceased","1415":"1415","Abt 1350":"about 1350","1324":"1324","1330":"1330","Abt 1324":"about 1324","1350":"1350","1294":"1294","England":"England, United Kingdom","<Of, Lackham, Wiltshire, England>":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Blewet","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): nickname from Old French <i>bleuet</i>, <i>blouet</i> ‘bluish’, a diminutive of <i>bleu</i> ‘blue’, more specifically ‘pale, pallid, wan’, or ‘fair-haired, golden-haired’. Compare   Blew  ,   Blewitt  , and   Bluett  .","History: The Norman Ralph Bloet is mentioned in Domesday Book (1086) as lord of the manor of Hinton in Hampshire, recorded in 1246 as <i>Henton Bluet</i> (modern Hinton Blewett). From the late 12th century onward many Anglo-Norman knights acquired estates in Ireland. Ralph's presumed descendants, Thomas and Ralph Bluet, held lands in counties Cork and Limerick before and after 1254, and are ancestors of the modern Irish families named Bluett, Blewett, and Blewitt. In 1850, following the Irish Potato Famine in Ireland (1845–49), Patrick Blewitt, a son of Edward Blewitt of Ballina, County Mayo, migrated to North America, his whole family joining him in 1851 to settle in Scranton PA. Joe Biden (see   Biden  ), the 46th president of the US, is Edward's great-great-great grandson."],"variants":[{"name":"Blewitt","meanings":["English: variant of   Blewett  ."]},{"name":"Bluett","meanings":["English (Cornwall): variant of   Blewett  ."]},{"name":"Blew","meanings":["Americanized form of German and Jewish (Ashkenazic)   Blau   ‘blue’. Compare   Blue  .","English: from Middle English <i>blew(e)</i>, a variant of <i>bleu</i> ‘blue’ (Old French <i>bleu</i>), ‘pale, pallid, wan’ (of complexion), or ‘fair, golden’ (of hair). Compare   Blewett  ."]},{"name":"Biden","meanings":["English (Hampshire and Surrey): habitational name, probably from Baydon (Wiltshire). The placename may have meant ‘hill associated with a woman named Bēage’ (a personal name derived from Old English <i>bēag</i> ‘ring, bracelet, torque’ + Old English <i>dūn</i>). The surname is pronounced /'baidən/.","History: The surname <i>Biden</i> has a long history in East Meon (Hampshire), recorded there from 1327 until at least the 1840s. — Joe Biden, the 46th president of the US, is of Irish, English, and French descent. His mother’s Jean (Catherine Eugenia) Finnegan entire family tree traces back to Ireland, with some of the ancestors named Blewitt (see   Blewett  )."]},{"name":"Bluitt","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Blewett  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Elinora","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor ."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elinora Blewet was born about 1324, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of John Blewet. She had at least 1 son with Edmond Baynard."},"et":{"Abt 1324–":"umbes 1324–Surnud","1324–Female":"1324–Surnud","1330–1350":"1330–1350","1350–1415":"1350–1415","1294–Male":"1294–Surnud","1415":"1415","Abt 1350":"umbes 1350","1324":"1324","1330":"1330","Abt 1324":"umbes 1324","1350":"1350","1294":"1294","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","<Of, Lackham, Wiltshire, England>":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1324–":"noin 1324–Kuollut","1324–Female":"1324–Kuollut","1330–1350":"1330–1350","1350–1415":"1350–1415","1294–Male":"1294–Kuollut","1415":"1415","Abt 1350":"noin 1350","1324":"1324","1330":"1330","Abt 1324":"noin 1324","1350":"1350","1294":"1294","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","<Of, Lackham, Wiltshire, England>":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1324–":"environ 1324–Décédée","1324–Female":"1324–Décédée","1330–1350":"1330–1350","1350–1415":"1350–1415","1294–Male":"1294–Décédé","1415":"1415","Abt 1350":"environ 1350","1324":"1324","1330":"1330","Abt 1324":"environ 1324","1350":"1350","1294":"1294","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","<Of, Lackham, Wiltshire, England>":"Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Elinora Blewet est née environ 1324, à Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fille de John Blewet. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Edmond Baynard."},"de":{"Abt 1324–":"um 1324–Verstorben","1324–Female":"1324–Verstorben","1330–1350":"1330–1350","1350–1415":"1350–1415","1294–Male":"1294–Verstorben","1415":"1415","Abt 1350":"um 1350","1324":"1324","1330":"1330","Abt 1324":"um 1324","1350":"1350","1294":"1294","England":"England, United Kingdom","<Of, Lackham, Wiltshire, England>":"Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Elinora Blewet wurde um 1324 in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, als Tochter von John Blewet geboren. Sie hatte mit 